description: Provides visibility into security events, access logs, and potential issues across your serverless architecture.

targets.expression:
filter status<=399
| fields @timestamp, @message, @xrayTraceId, requestId, ip, apiKey, requestTime, httpMethod, routeKey, path, status, protocol, integrationStatus, integrationLatency, responseLatency, responseLength
| parse @message "(*) *" as @requestId, restOfMessage
| parse restOfMessage "Method completed with status: *" as @status
| parse restOfMessage "Received response. Status: *, Integration latency: * ms" as responseStatus, jsonIntegrationLatency
| parse restOfMessage "X-ray Tracing ID : Root=*" as @xrayTraceId
| filter requestId like /${api_gtwy_request_id}/
| sort @timestamp desc
| limit ${limit}

panels.description: Returns the last 25 4-500 errors in your API Gateway access log group.

targets.expression:
filter status>=400 and status<=599
| fields @timestamp, @message, @xrayTraceId, requestId, ip, apiKey, requestTime, httpMethod, routeKey, path, status, protocol, integrationStatus, integrationLatency, responseLatency, responseLength
| parse @message "(*) *" as @requestId, restOfMessage
| parse restOfMessage "Method completed with status: *" as @status
| parse restOfMessage "Received response. Status: *, Integration latency: * ms" as responseStatus, jsonIntegrationLatency
| parse restOfMessage "X-ray Tracing ID : Root=*" as @xrayTraceId
| sort @timestamp desc
| limit 25

panels.title: 🔴API-Gateway: 4-500 errors🚨 (Last 25)💒

targets.expression:
fields @timestamp, @message, @xrayTraceId, correlation_id, @requestId, LogLevel, @duration, @billedDuration, @initDuration, @memorySize, @memoryUsed, @maxMemoryUsed, @type
| parse @message "START RequestId: * Version: *" as requestId, @version
| sort @timestamp desc
| filter correlation_id like /${api_gtwy_request_id}/
| limit ${limit}

targets.expression:
filter userIdentity.type not like /AssumedRole/
| filter eventName not like /AssumeRole/
| filter userIdentity.invokedBy not like /cloudtrail.amazonaws.com/
| fields @timestamp, @logStream, @message, eventVersion, userIdentity.type, coalesce(userIdentity.invokedBy, userIdentity.principalId, userIdentity.accountId) as InvokedBy, eventTime, eventSource, eventName, eventType, awsRegion, sourceIPAddress, userAgent, errorCode, errorMessage, eventID, @requestParameters, additionalEventData, requestID, readOnly, eventType, apiVersion, managementEvent, recipientAccountId, recipientAccountId.serviceEventDetails.serviceAccountId, eventCategory, tlsDetails.tlsVersion, tlsDetails.cipherSuite, tlsDetails.clientProvidedHostHeader
| sort @timestamp desc
| limit ${limit}
